I can’t apply the edit in this session because this workspace is read-only and `frontend/src/styles` does not currently exist in the checked-out tree, so there are no in-scope files to modify.

If you want, I can apply immediately once write access is available. Proposed change (create `frontend/src/styles/base.css` in that scope):

```css
:root {
  --font-stack: "Avenir Next", "Nunito Sans", "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
  --bg: #f8fafc;
  --surface: #ffffff;
  --text: #0b1120;
  --subtle: #526079;
  --line: #d8e0eb;
  --brand: #2a5bd7;
  --brand-soft: #e8f0ff;
  --error: #7f1d1d;
  --error-surface: #fef2f2;
  --spacing-1: 0.25rem;
  --spacing-2: 0.5rem;
  --spacing-3: 0.75rem;
  --spacing-4: 1rem;
  --spacing-5: 1.5rem;
  --spacing-6: 2rem;
  --radius: 0.6rem;
}

*,
*::before,
*::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-stack);
  color: var(--text);
  background: var(--bg);
}

.app-shell {
  max-width: min(72rem, 92vw);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
}

.stack {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-4);
}

.panel {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--line);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  padding: var(--spacing-5);
}

.panel h1,
.panel h2,
.panel h3,
.panel p {
  margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-3);
}

.panel h1 {
  font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.4vw, 1.9rem);
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.panel h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
  line-height: 1.3;
}

.panel p {
  color: var(--subtle);
  font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 1.6vw, 1rem);
  line-height: 1.55;
}

.state-panel {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  min-height: 16rem;
  text-align: center;
  gap: var(--spacing-3);
  padding: var(--spacing-6);
  border: 1px dashed var(--line);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
}

.state-title {
  font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
  font-weight: 650;
}

.state-message {
  max-width: 42ch;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.state-loading {
  color: var(--subtle);
}

.state-loading::before {
  content: "";
  width: 1.5rem;
  height: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 3px solid var(--line);
  border-top-color: var(--brand);
  animation: spin 0.7s linear infinite;
  display: inline-block;
  margin-inline-end: var(--spacing-2);
  vertical-align: text-bottom;
}

.state-error {
  color: var(--error);
  background: var(--error-surface);
  border-color: color-mix(in hsl, var(--error) 30%, var(--line) 70%);
}

.state-error .state-title {
  color: var(--error);
}

.btn {
  appearance: none;
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background: var(--brand);
  color: #ffffff;
  font-family: inherit;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding: 0.55rem 1rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: transform 120ms ease, box-shadow 120ms ease, background-color 120ms ease;
}

.btn:hover {
  background: color-mix(in hsl, var(--brand) 88%, black 12%);
}

.btn:active {
  transform: translateY(1px);
}

.btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 3px solid color-mix(in hsl, var(--brand) 30%, white 70%);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.btn:disabled {
  opacity: 0.65;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}

@keyframes spin {
  to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .state-panel {
    min-height: 12rem;
    padding: var(--spacing-5);
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}
```

If you want, reply with write-permitted access (or point me to the exact existing frontend path), and I’ll apply this directly.
